The clock ticks again with 24: LEGACY, the next evolution of the Emmy Award-winning â€œ24.â€ From Emmy Award-winning executive producer Howard Gordon (â€œHomeland,â€ â€œ24: Live Another Dayâ€), Academy Award- and Emmy Award-winning executive producer Brian Grazer (â€œA Beautiful Mind,â€ â€œ24â€), writers and executive producers Manny Coto and Evan Katz (â€œ24,â€ â€œ24: Live Another Dayâ€), director and executive producer Stephen Hopkins (â€œ24â€) and executive producer and original series star Kiefer Sutherland, 24: LEGACY chronicles an adrenaline-fueled race against the clock to stop a devastating terrorist attack on United States soil â€“ in the same real-time format that has propelled this genre-defining series. 

Six months ago in Yemen, an elite squad of U.S. Army Rangers, led by Sergeant ERIC CARTER (Corey Hawkins, â€œStraight Outta Comptonâ€), killed terrorist leader Sheik Ibrahim Bin-Khalid. In the aftermath, Bin-Khalidâ€™s followers declared a fatwah against Carter, his squad and their families, forcing them into federal witness protection. But a recent attempt on Carterâ€™s own life makes it clear to him that his team is now exposed. To thwart further attacks, Carter enlists REBECCA INGRAM (Miranda Otto, â€œHomelandâ€), who quarterbacked the raid that killed Bin-Khalid. Sheâ€™s a brilliant and ambitious intelligence officer who has stepped down from her post as National Director of CTU to support her husband, SENATOR JOHN DONOVAN (Emmy and Golden Globe Award winner Jimmy Smits, â€œNYPD Blue,â€ â€œThe West Wingâ€), in his campaign for President of the United States. Decades of sleepless nights and missed anniversaries landed her at the top. With the White House within their grasp, can she truly embrace a new role as First Lady? Or will her love of the action draw her back in? Together, in this fast-paced thrill ride, Carter and Ingram uncover a sophisticated terrorist network that will force them to ask: â€œWho can we trust?â€ As they battle Bin-Khalidâ€™s devotees, they are forced to confront their own identities, families and pasts.

title: TV Series Recommendation- 24
description:
ðŸŽ¥ Looking for new TV show to watch? You have to check out the series, 24. Itâ€™s currently my favorite series. 

24 stars Kiefer Sutherland as US counter terrorist agent Jack Bauer. Each season takes place within a 24 hour timeframe, with each episode occurring in real time, within one hour of that day (ex: an episode would be 2:00am-3:00am and so forth).

The show depicts Jack Bauer and the Counter Terrorism Unit (CTU) dealing with presidential assassination attempts, bomb threats, kidnapping, political corruption, nuclear, biological, and cyber warfare, and more. 

Itâ€™s intense, fast-paced, action packed, and youâ€™ll want to keep watching. The show ran for 9 seasons and also includes a television film, 24: Redemption that bridges the sixth and seventh seasons. In 2017 24 was revived with a 12-episode spinoff, 24:Legacy.

Cool Facts About 24
- it is the longest running US espionage or counter-terrorism themed television drama

- consistently cited as one of the best shows on television 

- 24 is one of only five tv shows to win an Emmy, Golden Globe, and Satellite award for Best Drama Series

- The series received 68 Emmy nominations, with 20 wins, along with dozens of other awards.

- In 2008, Empire magazine ranked 24 as the sixth-greatest television show of all time

- There is an Indian and Japanese adaptation of 24

title: Russian Trade - 24 Live Another Day - Final Scene
description:
Here are Jack Bauer's final moments, in 24 Live Another Day. Sets up a strange story line giving the possibility of we might get to see Bauer again perhaps in Legacy. The writers couldn't bring themselves to kill off Jack Bauer, resulting in this conflicted ending for LAD. 

Here Chloe & Jack are trading their places with the Russians. In the same episode as Audrey's death. From seeing the promos for this episode and seeing the casket. I was certain it would be Jack with the death ending. Given the time jump. But the UK promo was released which stumped me as it showed a second from this scene with Jack and Chloe meeting, in daylight. So if the time jump occurred and he was still alive it twisted my mind for this.

Chloe receives a piece of paper off Jack, presumably with a note on it. Which she takes back and is an excellent set up for the future of 24. Always great to see Belcheck as well.

Best Quotes!

"If anything happens to her, or my family. Your entire world will come apart"

"We just want you Mr Bauer, that's all we ever wanted"

title: Jack Bauer & President Palmer's Final Conversation - 24 Season 4 Finale
description:
After the 'bromance' showcased in the first 4 series of the show it has come to the point in the Season 4 Finale in which it shows us the last ever scene between Jack Bauer and President David Palmer. However this was unknown to the viewer at the time. Palmer mentions this could be the last time they ever speak. Jack then delivers his final lines to Palmer ''Mr President, its been an honor''. Marking a close to the season and Jack walks out into the sunset as Season 4 concludes. 

This scene has some relevance now as Kiefer Sutherland recently got cast as the President of a new drama series on ABC called 'Designated Survivor', I will be uploading clips from that show too once it begins airing. Also expect clips from other shows containing 24 Cast members to come on this channel.

title: Edgar Stiles Death - 24 Season 5
description:
Here is another heart wrenching scene. This time it is the lovable Edgar Stiles who bites the bullet. After CTU is under attack in mid-season 5 from nerve gasses. Jack and the other main characters hide out in the situation room, which is sealed up avoiding any of the gasses to enter. However at this time Edgar was sent off to check up on Carrie. By the time he got back it was too late, he had already been effected by the nerve gas. His final word is ''Chloe'', as he stares at her through the glass. These two characters had a lot of tension between them in both Season 4 & 5. This shortly disappeared in this scene, where you can see how Chloe cares for Edgar. Edgar also receives the fifth silent clock in the series.

title: 24: The TV Masterpiece That Disappeared
description:
24 was one of the most revolutionary action series in television history. This video is both a love letter and a call to action â€” a plea to bring back the show that defined real-time storytelling.

While there have been a lot of shows and movies rebooted over the years, but there remains one series in particular that has, sadly, never been brought back to life, and that is 24. Hands down, one of the most action-packed television dramas of the 21st century. It truly pains me to see a show like 24 just disappear from almost all mainstream relevance. 

This is my video on why it should come back.

What is 24?

24 is an American action drama television series created by Joel Surnow and Robert Cochran for Fox. The series stars Kiefer Sutherland as US counter-terrorist federal agent Jack Bauer. Each season covers 24 consecutive hours in Bauer's life using the real time method of narration, which is emphasized by the display of split screens and a digital clock. The show premiered on November 6, 2001, and spanned 204 episodes over nine seasons, with the series finale broadcast on July 14, 2014. In addition, the television film 24: Redemption aired between seasons six and seven, on November 23, 2008. 24 is a joint production by Imagine Television and 20th Century Fox Television.

title: The ENTIRE Story of 24 Season 1 in Under 5 Minutes
description:
The ENTIRE story of 24 Season 1 in under 5 minutes

At exactly midnight in Los Angeles, counter-terrorism agent Jack Bauer is pulled back into the field. Thereâ€™s a credible threat: someone is planning to assassinate Senator David Palmer, a front-runner for the presidency. Palmer is the first Black man with a serious chance at the Oval Officeâ€”and someone doesnâ€™t want him to get there.

But thatâ€™s only half the story.

Jack isnâ€™t just an agent. Heâ€™s a husband. A father. And as the day begins, heâ€™s trying to repair a fractured marriage with his wife Teri while keeping tabs on their rebellious teenage daughter Kim. But before he even gets to CTU headquarters, Kim sneaks out of the houseâ€”and straight into a nightmare.

At CTU, Jack is told thereâ€™s a mole inside the agency. Someone feeding information to the people behind the assassination attempt. Heâ€™s given a warning: Trust no one. Not even the people closest to him.

That includes Nina Myers, his colleague and former lover, and Tony Almeida, a smart, sharp analyst with his own doubts about Jackâ€™s judgment. As the night unfolds, Jack realizes the threat is deeper than he thought. The people behind it are organized, well-funded, and willing to kill anyone who stands in their way.

Meanwhile, Kim finds herself kidnapped by two men who pretend to be friendly, only to trap her in a twisted plan. Teri, searching for her daughter, ends up captured too. Suddenly, Jackâ€™s family becomes leverageâ€”and the attackers force Jack into an impossible choice: follow orders, or watch his family die.

He plays alongâ€”at first. But Jack Bauer doesnâ€™t follow rules for long. He fakes compliance, tracks leads, and slowly begins unravelling the network of conspirators. He uncovers clues: a suicide that wasnâ€™t a suicide. A connection to a covert U.S. operation in Kosovo. And a name: Drazen.

Victor Drazen.

Years ago, Jack led a black ops mission to eliminate Drazenâ€”a war criminal responsible for countless atrocities. The mission was successful. Or so they thought.

Now, Drazenâ€™s sons want revenge. And Jack Bauer is their main target.

But they donâ€™t just want to kill him. They want him to suffer. And that means using Kim and Teri as pawns. The attackers stage a series of traps and fakeouts. Jack breaks laws, breaks into police custody, and even breaks down emotionallyâ€”but he keeps going.

David Palmer, meanwhile, is dealing with his own crisis. His son was involved in a cover-up, and the truth threatens to derail his campaign. His wife, Sherry, is willing to lie, spin, and manipulate to keep the campaign aliveâ€”but Palmer refuses to compromise his integrity. As the day progresses, Palmer is testedâ€”not just politically, but morally. He learns what it means to lead under pressure. And what it costs.

Back at CTU, suspicions rise. A second assassination attempt is foiled, but the threat escalates. Jack learns that Victor Drazen is still alive, held secretly by the U.S. government. The attackers want a trade: Victor for Kim.

Itâ€™s a trapâ€”but Jack has no choice.

He delivers Drazen, only to be double-crossed again. A violent shootout follows, and Jack barely survives. But heâ€™s not done.

In the final hours of the day, Jack storms the Drazens' location in a brutal assault. One by one, he eliminates them. The revenge plot ends in blood. Jack rescues Kim. Finallyâ€”finallyâ€”it seems like the nightmare is over.

But 24 doesnâ€™t end with a happy reunion.

Thereâ€™s still one more betrayal.

Throughout the day, Jack trusted Nina Myers. She was by his side. She helped him track leads. She supported him at every turn.

Until now.

Itâ€™s revealed that Nina is the mole. The one feeding intel to the enemy from the start. Sheâ€™s been playing both sides the entire time. And as Jack races back to CTU to stop her, Nina does something unforgivable.

She murders Teri Bauer.

Jack arrives moments too late. He finds his wifeâ€™s body in a CTU storeroom. The woman he spent all day trying to protect is gone.

24 Season 1 synopsis.

title: All 10 Seasons of 24 Ranked & Reviewed Worst to Best!  (including 24: Legacy)
description:
24 is one of my favorite TV shows of all time.  With the first season of 24: Legacy coming to a close, it seemed like the perfect time to rank all 10 seasons of 24!

All 10 seasons of 24 ranked and reviewed worst to best!

24 Season 1 (2001 - 2002)
24 Season 2 (2002 - 2003)
24 Season 3 (2003 - 2004)
24 Season 4 (2005)
24 Season 5 (2006)
24 Season 6 (2007)
24 Season 7 (2009)
24 Season 8 (2010)
24 Live Another Day (2014)
24: Legacy (2017)

Season 1 Synopsis
The first season takes place on the day of the California Presidential Primary.

The season's main plot revolves around an assassination attempt on U.S. Senator from Maryland, David Palmer, a candidate for the Democratic Party presidential nomination, on the day of the primary in California. The central character is Jack Bauer, a former Delta Force operator who is the Director of the fictional Counter Terrorist Unit (CTU) in Los Angeles. Bauer becomes professionally as well as personally involved when his wife Teri and daughter Kim are kidnapped by the people behind the assassination plot.

24: Live Another Day Synopsis
Live Another Day takes place four years after the events of season 8. James Heller, now President, is negotiating a treaty in London, where a hacker collective preaching freedom of information has enlisted the help of Chloe O'Brian. Jack Bauer, who has been tracking the activities of Chloe's group while living in exile, resurfaces when he hears of an imminent attempt on Heller's life.

24 Legacy
After leading a mission to eliminate terrorist leader Sheikh Ibrahim bin-Khalid, Eric Carter (Corey Hawkins) returns to the U.S. and finds out that he and his squad mates are targeted for assassination in retaliation for bin-Khalid's supposed death. With nowhere else to turn, Carter asks CTU to help him save his life while also stopping one of the largest-scale terror attacks on American soil. The series takes place three years after the events of 24: Live Another Day and is set in Washington, D.C.

title: 24 - The Most Stressful Clock In TV History
description: 24 is an American television series produced for the Fox network and syndicated worldwide, starring Kiefer Sutherland as Counter Terrorist Unit (CTU) agent Jack Bauer. Each 24-episode season covers 24 hours in the life of Bauer, using the real time method of narration. Premiering on November 6, 2001, the show spanned 192 episodes over eight seasons, with the series finale broadcast on May 24, 2010. In addition, a television film, 24: Redemption, was broadcast between seasons six and seven. Fox announced in May 2013 that 24 would return as a 12-episode series titled 24: Live Another Day which debuted on May 5, 2014.[2][3]
